definition: to fill a gap/to fill in a blank (on a form)/to overcome a deficiency
to fill or stuff/(of a form etc) to fill in
to repair/to patch/to mend/to make up for/to fill (a vacancy)/to supplement

sentences.english: Unemployment and unfilled vacancies can exist side by side .
sentences.chinese: 失業和未填補的空額可以同時並存。

sentences.english: Unconsciously and unintentionally we fill up the gaps and supplement the dream-images.
sentences.chinese: 我們會不自覺地填補夢境中未被憶起的空白。

sentences.english: Uncover the starting and ending points and start filling in the blanks one at a time.
sentences.chinese: 找到起始點，然後開始填補空白。

sentences.english: Shea filled in for Brown at right-back.
sentences.chinese: 奧謝則填補了布朗右邊的空缺。

sentences.english: This book fills a major gap in lexicography.
sentences.chinese: 這本書填補了詞典學方面的重大缺門。

sentences.english: Nor can investment rise to fill the gap.
sentences.chinese: 依靠投資增長來填補空缺也是不可能的。

sentences.english: I have something very unique to discuss with readers- the spirituality of work.
sentences.chinese: 很少友人談論這個，因此我知道我填補了這個空白。

sentences.english: The utility model fills the blank of the special tank car for transporting the bulk dry-mixed mortar in China.
sentences.chinese: 填補了國內幹混砂漿無散裝運輸專用罐車的空白。

sentences.english: So, again, someone must fill the hole.
sentences.chinese: 因此，有人必須再一次填補這個窟窿。

sentences.english: To fill the gap left by what Gehlen called instinctual deprivation. people create social frameworks.
sentences.chinese: 爲了填補留下的空白什麼蓋倫所謂本能剝奪。

sentences.english: He legislates only between gaps. He fills the open spaces in the law.
sentences.chinese: 他只是在空白處立法，他填補着法律中的空缺地帶。

sentences.english: But the bond market and loans between companies filled some of the gap.
sentences.chinese: 但是債券市場和公司之間的貸款填補了一些空缺。

sentences.english: Fill in nail holes in drywall with  toothpaste and baking soda.
sentences.chinese: 牙膏與小蘇打混合可以用來填補牆面的釘子洞。

sentences.english: This funding gap must be filled.
sentences.chinese: 這一資助差額必須加以填補。

sentences.english: There is a small cavity to be filled.
sentences.chinese: 有個蛀齒的小洞要填補。

sentences.english: It's a cold winter day and the room is filled with the aroma of incense.
sentences.chinese: 這是一個寒冷的冬天，房間是與香香氣填補。

definition: to complement/to make up for a deficiency
to bring up to full strength/to make up a deficiency/to fill (a vacancy, gap etc)
to transfer/to maneuver (troops etc)/movement of personnel/to mobilize/to bring into play
one's conduct/deed/activity/accomplishment/achievement/to act as/as (in the capacity of)/qua/to view as/to look upon (sth as)/to take sth to be
for this reason/with regards to this/in this respect/in order to do this/to this end
to break away from/to cast off (old ideas etc)/to get rid of/to break away (from)/to break out (of)/to free oneself from/to extricate oneself
to overlap/to superimpose/to telescope/to run together/to duplicate/one over another/superposition/an overlap/redundancy/reduplication (in Chinese grammar, e.g. 散散步[san4 san4 bu4] to have a stroll)
